[4] Funding
- Cases, drugs, funding
6 Jun 2018. DRC probes 5 new possible Ebola cases; WHO details experimental drugs
[Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy (CIDRAP), edited]
http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2018/06/drc-probes-5-new-possible-ebola-cases-who-details-experimental-drugs
[byline: Lisa Schnirring]

[The article covers cases and experimental drugs, both reported above, so not included here. What is reported here is a welcome reversal by the Trump administration to maintain Ebola response funds. - Mod.LK]

White House reverses taking away Ebola funds
--------------------------------------------
The Trump Administration yesterday [5 Jun 2018] removed cuts in Ebola funding, along with a few other items, from its proposed budget rescissions yesterday, Roll Call reported. The Ebola money targeted for cuts last month [May 2018] was USD 252 million in unspent funds that the last administration had allocated for West Africa's Ebola outbreak, funding that was meant to help countries at risk for the disease improve their health and emergency response systems.

The originally proposed rescissions were first announced in early May 2018, as news was emerging of the current DRC outbreak, for which the US Agency for International Development (USAID) has contributed up to USD 8 million. The Trump Administration has praised the DRC for allocating its own funds and other countries for their significant contributions to the response.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail rapporteur Mary Marshall

[This is welcome news, but there should exist a protected readily available preparedness fund to address outbreaks of any agent. These events are not diminishing, but rather increasing - such as mosquitoborne agents West Nile, chikungunya, Zika; zoonotic diseases MERS, SARS, Nipah, Lassa, in addition to Ebola. The US ramped up its response to terrorists, but nature provides the greatest challenge to our safety and remains unpredictable. We only know we will experience more infectious disease events against which we must be prepared before they re/emerge. - Mod.LK

